OL,3,CReport into NHS blood scandal due to
OL,4,Cbe published
OL,6,FA public inquiry is due to publish its
OL,7,Ffindings into the infected blood
OL,8,Fscandal, which has become known as the
OL,9,Fworst treatment disaster in NHS
OL,10,Fhistory.
OL,12,FTens of thousands of people were
OL,13,Finfected with contaminated blood
OL,14,Fproducts or blood transfusions between
OL,15,Fthe 1970s and early 1990s.
OL,17,FAn estimated 3,000 people have died as
OL,18,Fa result, while those who survived
OL,19,Fhave lived with life-long health
OL,20,Fimplications.
